efficiently and easily cope with extremely large amounts of data. PyTables
is built on top of the HDF5 library, using the Python language and the
NumPy package.

about.summary: Brings together Python, HDF5 and NumPy to easily handle large amounts of data.

name: pytables
raw_recipe:
{% set version="3.4.1" %}

package:
  name: pytables
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: PyTables-v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://github.com/PyTables/PyTables/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 1fed6fe6f1b76b3e123bae44e37199be8e915d53ce270740f63a29a04a5db7c5

build:
  number: 0
  entry_points:
    - pt2to3 = tables.scripts.pt2to3:main
    - ptdump = tables.scripts.ptdump:main
    - ptrepack = tables.scripts.ptrepack:main
    - pttree = tables.scripts.pttree:main

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - cython
    - numpy x.x
    - zlib 1.2.*
    - lzo 2.06  # [linux]
    - bzip2 1.0.*
    - hdf5 1.8.17|1.8.17.*
    - numexpr
    # Building blosc is done internally. The version is up-to-date.
    # - blosc
  run:
    - python
    - six
    - numpy x.x
    - numexpr
    - hdf5 1.8.17|1.8.17.*
    - zlib 1.2.*
    - lzo 2.06  # [linux]
    - bzip2 1.0.*
    # building blosc is done internally. The version is up-to-date.
    # - blosc

test:
  requires:
    - setuptools
  commands:
    - pt2to3 -h
    - ptdump -h
    - ptrepack -h
    - pttree -h
    - conda inspect linkages -p $PREFIX pytables  # [not win]
    - conda inspect objects -p $PREFIX pytables  # [osx]


about:
  home: http://www.pytables.org
  license: BSD 3-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: 'Brings together Python, HDF5 and NumPy to easily handle large amounts of data.'
  description: |
    PyTables is a package for managing hierarchical datasets and designed to
    efficiently and easily cope with extremely large amounts of data. PyTables
    is built on top of the HDF5 library, using the Python language and the
    NumPy package.
  doc_url: http://www.pytables.org/
  dev_url: https://github.com/PyTables

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - msarahan
    - ocefpaf
    - tomkooij
    - scopatz
